The abducted aged mother of the All Progressives Congress (APC) Kano Central Senatorial District candidate, AA Zaura, has been rescued by the operatives of the Department of State Services, DSS in Jigawa State. Hajia Laure Mai Kunu was abducted by some gunmen who had stormed Zaura town of Nassarawa Local Government in Kano State in the early hours of Monday. Reports have it that Hajia Laure was abducted from her House at Zaura village some five kilometers away from the main city center. Chairman of Ungogo Local Government Area, Engr. Abdullahi Garba Ramat, who confirmed the development, said the security agents have not informed him officially of the incident. However, a top DSS operative who did not want his name in print, confirmed that their men had rescued Laure and another aged woman who was abducted almost ten days ago, Daily Post reports He said, “it is true that we have rescued Laure in Jigawa State, this followed a serious tip-off by our men. We traced her in Jigawa and rescued her unhurt”. The DSS further narrated that while rescuing her, they found another old woman whose ransom of N2 million was already paid out of the requested N10 million and rescued her.